ompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/freq2MIDI.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Frequency to MIDI note number — freq2MIDI","text":"","code":"freq2MIDI(freq)"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/freq2MIDI.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Frequency to MIDI note number — freq2MIDI","text":"freq numeric vector frequency values","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/freq2MIDI.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Frequency to MIDI note number — freq2MIDI","text":"numeric vector corresponding MIDI note numbers","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/freq2MIDI.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Frequency to MIDI note number — freq2MIDI","text":"","code":"# chromatic scale   freq <- 2 ^ (seq(0, 12) / 12) * 220   print(freq2MIDI(freq)) #>  [1] 57 58 59 60 61 62 63 64 65 66 67 68 69"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/period_reduce.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","title":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","text":"Reduce vector ratios given period","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/period_reduce.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","text":"","code":"period_reduce(scale, period = 2)"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/period_reduce.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","text":"scale numeric vector ratios representing scale period period scale - default 2.0, \"octave\"","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/period_reduce.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","text":"scale reduced ratios 1 period","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/period_reduce.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Period Reduce — period_reduce","text":"","code":"test_scale <- cents2ratio(seq(2400, 3500, by = 100))   print(scale <- period_reduce(test_scale, 2)) #>  [1] 1.000000 1.059463 1.122462 1.189207 1.259921 1.334840 1.414214 1.498307 #>  [9] 1.587401 1.681793 1.781797 1.887749"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/prodset_scale_table.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","title":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","text":"Creates scale table product set definition","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/prodset_scale_table.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","text":"","code":"prodset_scale_table(prodset_def, period = 2, tonic_note_number = 60)"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/prodset_scale_table.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","text":"prodset_def product set scale definition. list numeric vectors. vector multiset number integers. example, prodset_def 1-3-5-7 Hexany list(c(1, 3), c(1, 5), c(1, 7), c(3, 5), c(3, 7), c(5, 7)) period period scale - default 2. tonic_note_number MIDI note number tonic scale - default middle C = 60","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/prodset_scale_table.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","text":"data.table seven columns: ratio: ratio defines note, number 1 period ratio_frac: ratio vulgar fraction (character). ratios type scale usually irrational, approximation, computed fractional::fractional. ratio_cents: ratio cents (hundredths semitone) frequency: frequency note given tonic_note_number parameter bent_midi: MIDI note number integer plus fraction. example, middle C MIDI note number 60 middle C sharp 61. quarter-tone half-way C C sharp bent_midi value 60.5. name bent_midi comes fact MIDI sequencer can convert value regular integer MIDI note number message pitch bend message. interval_cents: interval note previous note degree: scale degree zero (number notes) - 1","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/prodset_scale_table.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Create Product Set Scale Table — prodset_scale_table","text":"","code":"(hexany <- prodset_scale_table(list(   c(1, 3),   c(1, 5),   c(1, 7),   c(3, 5),   c(3, 7),   c(5, 7) ))) #> Key: <ratio> #>       ratio ratio_frac ratio_cents frequency bent_midi interval_cents degree #>       <num> <charFrac>       <num>     <num>     <num>          <num>  <num> #> 1: 1.000000          1      0.0000  261.6256  60.00000             NA      0 #> 2: 1.166667        7/6    266.8709  305.2298  62.66871      266.87091      1 #> 3: 1.250000        5/4    386.3137  327.0320  63.86314      119.44281      2 #> 4: 1.458333      35/24    653.1846  381.5373  66.53185      266.87091      3 #> 5: 1.666667        5/3    884.3587  436.0426  68.84359      231.17409      4 #> 6: 1.750000        7/4    968.8259  457.8447  69.68826       84.46719      5 #> 7: 2.000000          2   1200.0000  523.2511  72.00000      231.17409      0"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2cents.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","title":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","text":"Converts vector ratios vector corresponding cents values","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2cents.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","text":"","code":"ratio2cents(ratio)"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2cents.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","text":"ratio numeric vector ratios","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2cents.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","text":"numeric vector corresponding cents values","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2cents.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Ratio to Cents — ratio2cents","text":"","code":"i <- seq(0, 12)   print(ratio2cents(2.0 ^ (i / 12.0))) #>  [1]    0  100  200  300  400  500  600  700  800  900 1000 1100 1200"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2factors.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","title":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","text":"Converts vector ratios vector corresponding integer factors.","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2factors.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","text":"","code":"ratio2factors(ratio)"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2factors.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","text":"ratio numeric vector ratios","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2factors.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","text":"list vectors, vector integer factors determined corresponding ratio","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/ratio2factors.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Ratio to Factors — ratio2factors","text":"","code":"print(super <- sclfile_scale_table(system.file(   \"test_scl_files/carlos_super.scl\",   package = \"consonaR\" ))$scale_table) #> Key: <ratio_cents> #>     degree ratio_cents ratio_frac frequency interval_cents interval_frac #>      <num>       <num> <charFrac>     <num>          <num>    <charFrac> #>  1:      0      0.0000          1  261.6256             NA           1/0 #>  2:      1    104.9554      17/16  277.9772      104.95541         17/16 #>  3:      2    203.9100        9/8  294.3288       98.95459         18/17 #>  4:      3    315.6413        6/5  313.9507      111.73129         16/15 #>  5:      4    386.3137        5/4  327.0320       70.67243         25/24 #>  6:      5    498.0450        4/3  348.8341      111.73129         16/15 #>  7:      6    551.3179       11/8  359.7352       53.27294         33/32 #>  8:      7    701.9550        3/2  392.4383      150.63706         12/11 #>  9:      8    840.5277       13/8  425.1415      138.57266         13/12 #> 10:      9    884.3587        5/3  436.0426       43.83105         40/39 #> 11:     10    968.8259        7/4  457.8447       84.46719         21/20 #> 12:     11   1088.2687       15/8  490.5479      119.44281         15/14 #> 13:      0   1200.0000          2  523.2511      111.73129         16/15 print(super_factors <- ratio2factors(cents2ratio(super$ratio_cents))) #> $`240` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 3 5 #>  #> $`255` #> [1]  3  5 17 #>  #> $`270` #> [1] 2 3 3 3 5 #>  #> $`288` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 2 3 3 #>  #> $`300` #> [1] 2 2 3 5 5 #>  #> $`320` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 2 2 5 #>  #> $`330` #> [1]  2  3  5 11 #>  #> $`360` #> [1] 2 2 2 3 3 5 #>  #> $`390` #> [1]  2  3  5 13 #>  #> $`400` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 5 5 #>  #> $`420` #> [1] 2 2 3 5 7 #>  #> $`450` #> [1] 2 3 3 5 5 #>  #> $`480` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 2 3 5 #>   print(harm <- sclfile_scale_table(system.file(   \"test_scl_files/carlos_harm.scl\",   package = \"consonaR\" ))$scale_table) #> Key: <ratio_cents> #>     degree ratio_cents ratio_frac frequency interval_cents interval_frac #>      <num>       <num> <charFrac>     <num>          <num>    <charFrac> #>  1:      0      0.0000          1  261.6256             NA           1/0 #>  2:      1    104.9554      17/16  277.9772      104.95541         17/16 #>  3:      2    203.9100        9/8  294.3288       98.95459         18/17 #>  4:      3    297.5130      19/16  310.6804       93.60301         19/18 #>  5:      4    386.3137        5/4  327.0320       88.80070         20/19 #>  6:      5    470.7809      21/16  343.3836       84.46719         21/20 #>  7:      6    551.3179       11/8  359.7352       80.53704         22/21 #>  8:      7    701.9550        3/2  392.4383      150.63706         12/11 #>  9:      8    840.5277       13/8  425.1415      138.57266         13/12 #> 10:      9    905.8650      27/16  441.4931       65.33734         27/26 #> 11:     10    968.8259        7/4  457.8447       62.96090         28/27 #> 12:     11   1088.2687       15/8  490.5479      119.44281         15/14 #> 13:      0   1200.0000          2  523.2511      111.73129         16/15 print(harm_factors <- ratio2factors(cents2ratio(harm$ratio_cents))) #> $`16` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 #>  #> $`17` #> [1] 17 #>  #> $`18` #> [1] 2 3 3 #>  #> $`19` #> [1] 19 #>  #> $`20` #> [1] 2 2 5 #>  #> $`21` #> [1] 3 7 #>  #> $`22` #> [1]  2 11 #>  #> $`24` #> [1] 2 2 2 3 #>  #> $`26` #> [1]  2 13 #>  #> $`27` #> [1] 3 3 3 #>  #> $`28` #> [1] 2 2 7 #>  #> $`30` #> [1] 2 3 5 #>  #> $`32` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 2 #>   # we know the factors that yield the 1-3-5-7 Hexany # can we recover them? (hexany <- prodset_scale_table(list(   c(1, 3),   c(1, 5),   c(1, 7),   c(3, 5),   c(3, 7),   c(5, 7) ))$ratio) #> [1] 1.000000 1.166667 1.250000 1.458333 1.666667 1.750000 2.000000 (hexany_factors <- ratio2factors(hexany)) #> $`24` #> [1] 2 2 2 3 #>  #> $`28` #> [1] 2 2 7 #>  #> $`30` #> [1] 2 3 5 #>  #> $`35` #> [1] 5 7 #>  #> $`40` #> [1] 2 2 2 5 #>  #> $`42` #> [1] 2 3 7 #>  #> $`48` #> [1] 2 2 2 2 3 #>"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/sclfile_scale_table.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Create Scale Table From a Scala .scl File — sclfile_scale_table","title":"Create Scale Table From a Scala .scl File — sclfile_scale_table","text":"Creates scale table given .scl file","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/sclfile_scale_table.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Create Scale Table From a Scala .scl File — sclfile_scale_table","text":"","code":"sclfile_scale_table(sclfile_path, root_freq = 440/(2^(9/12)))"},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/sclfile_scale_table.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Create Scale Table From a Scala .scl File — sclfile_scale_table","text":"sclfile_path path valid Scala .scl file root_freq root frequency scale - default middle C: 440 / (2 ^ (9 / 12))","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/sclfile_scale_table.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Create Scale Table From a Scala .scl File — sclfile_scale_table","text":"list two three items: status (character): \"Oll Korrect\" results valid, otherwise error message file_contents (character vector): contents read file scale_table (data.table): everything worked, scale table","code":""},{"path":"https://algocompsynth.github.io/consonaR/reference/sclfile_scale_table.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headin